    "body": "I have been unable to reproduce with a test. For whatever reason, libp2p is not cooperating with me.\r\n\r\nI have subscriber tests here: https://github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/blob/d4209b7357101642a17dd8e4f3326fe73c89c0bb/shared/p2p/service_test.go#L187\r\n\r\nThese currently send an empty message on a topic, just to see if the adapters run. The reason I am using an empty message is that if I pass a non-empty message then the test no longer works unless the test is run by it self. \r\n\r\n```bash\r\n# Works\r\nbazel test //shared/p2p:go_default_test --test_output=streamed --test_filter=TestRegisterTopic_withoutAdapters --cache_test_results=no\r\n\r\n# Does not work\r\nbazel test //shared/p2p:go_default_test --test_output=streamed  --cache_test_results=no\r\n```\r\n\r\nI have been toying on this for about a week now and making zero progress. I can't tell if it's something wrong with libp2p or our code, but it doesn't make any sense. \r\n\r\nI'll stop trying to reproduce in the test and just work on a fix for runtime. ",
