    "body": "I have identified the issue with reflect types. Since proto.Message is a pointer to the underlying struct, i.e. `*pb.BeaconBlockAnnounce`, and reflect.New creates a new pointer to the given type, we ended up with `**pb.BeaconBlockAnnounce` which ended up resolving to a nil ptr. \r\n\r\nI have the fix ready, I'm just trying to resolve new test breakages with libp2p. ",
